//upgrade User Tips:\n 1、The user’s default identity adopts ERC1056 protocol, which only allows single-address management.\n 2、Users can upgrade to aggregated identity using ERC1484 protocol, and then the multi-address management function will be enabled. The original address is set as the default address.\n 3、while call the ERC 1484 Protocol to upgrade identity, user must have enough eth in the address to pay for the transaction gas.\n 4、After upgrading to an aggregated identity, user can add any valid address as the associated address of the aggregated identity.\n 5、Each address can only be associated with one aggregated identity , and each aggregated identity has a recovery address.\n 6、The recovery address should be stored in a cold wallet. This app does not store any backup information related to the recovery address. Please be aware.\n 7、The recovery address can help you regain control of your aggregated identity if your wallet is stolen or accidentally lost. Redownload the app and click the "recover identity" button to go to the recovery page.\n 8、If your recovery address is maliciously misappropriated, please contact customer service immediately.\n
